  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Let's start gathering up our ideas for 11.05 for this page :)

___Contribute to open source tab___

Projects box: 
* Maybe show a link to bugs if there are some. Do we just show bitesize or all? 

Training missions:
* Show progress. This might mean some tinkering of the mission model. 

* I did see somewhere in code a way to list people that have completed it. Not 
sure if that'd be interesting but maybe? "Join 73 other people that have finished 
the SVN mission" or such.

* I would love to see a list of all missions dynamically so that we can say "new" 
or "updated?" or such. Again, might mean tinkering with the missions model unless 
I didn't understand the methods right.

People:

* Number of people shown should be limited to maybe 5?

* Add "mentors" list

___Attract contributors tab___

* It maybe should link to projects you're a part of, particular show the ones 
that have wannahelpers. - Asheesh

* It should maybe provide a 'nudge' to fill out the project page, if it's blank. 
- Asheesh

* If one of the projects doesn't have any Bug objects associated with it, it 
could (for now) link to the wiki page about adding a bug tracker. (Soon, maybe 
later today, there'll be an in-site UI for that.) - Asheesh 

* Maybe link to places/help on how to grow/maintain community? Ideas on where to 
find developers? Related to: <a href="https://openhatch.org/bugs/issue323">https://openhatch.org/bugs/issue323</a>

* Feature new developers? Or new user with contact information filled out that is 
interested in that language but maybe hasn't seen that project?

* Social networking tie-in? "Tweet this" for "Want to get started in open source? 
Gain fame, fortune (of praise)." + shortened url to their bitesize bugs on 
openhatch? with good hashtags? and how to set up a page on Facebook? Not sure 
about that. Or maybe which pages would be good to "advertise" on?

* List of colleges nearby with ACM chapters or area LUGS or again more "where to 
find people" type ideas.

* List of people that said "I wanna help" and a way to contact them. Related to: 
<a href="http://openhatch.org/bugs/issue282">http://openhatch.org/bugs/issue282</a> and <a href="http://openhatch.org/bugs/issue408">http://openhatch.org/bugs/issue408</a> 

 

Please add your ideas. We can always push some to later milestones but definitely 
hope we keep iteratively improving these landing pages :)</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
